		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Why AC is King<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Apr 8th 11:15 AM 2002 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=101827865294502&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=101827865294502&post=1&replyto=101827865294502"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=101827865294502></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=93579"><span id=>Yosa</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>263 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.58]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Say what you want, but in the end AC is King.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes other stats are important but not as important as AC and here is why.<br><br>Look at your starting numbers.  Str will be 100+ Sta, Dex, and Agi will be some where in that area.  If I recall your AC will be 20 or so.  <br><br>Str, dex etc are caped at 255. As far as I know there is no ac cap.  I know warriors with 1000+ ac and have herd that some have 1,200. <br><br>Buffing: at higher lvl it is easy to get +100 str dex, etc by buffing this is over 33% of you cap.  You get about 60 ac from a good buffing or less than 10% of your ac.   <br><br>In short you equipment is the only way to signiffently to increase your ac.  This is not the case for str etc.  <br><br>Ok so AC is King but is it not the only thing.  And how much do you need?  Depending on what role you want to play and the amount of time you have in game I think an ac of 900 (lvl 50+) is good enough.  If you could get it so that with your normal buffs it is over 1000 that is even better. <br><br>After ac for me str is most important.  This is because my normal groups don't have many damage dealers.  And more str means more damage, which means more taunt. I have been in groups with small race warriors that are higher lvl than my warrior, that have about the same weapons as I do, and if I don't down grade my weapons I hold agro, because of my higher str.  However when these warriors and I have both our str maxed buy buffng they can hold agro.   <br><br>For me after str I work on my dex.  This is because I have a weapon that porcs for 176hps<br><br>So what does this all mean?  <br>For me I don't automaticly traid ac for str, but I give it some thought, I will not traid dex for ac but I try to keep it at a minimun lvl.  </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
