		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I agree totally, however the one problem I have with the AC is king phrase is that people take it way out of hand.<br><br>I've seen people highly suggesting others NOT to go for other stats AT ALL. This mean if you had a choice between an item that was 6ac, +2 str, +2 sta +5svm and one that was 8ac, people would tell ya to go for the 8ac no stats.<br><br>It's all relative to what your stats already are and your common role. Obviously if your Str and Sta is already high I'd say maybe go with the 8ac item. But keep in mind you're not restricted to having just one piece of armour. You're a warrior with high str and with weight reduction bags you can carry around a crap load of stuff. Keep the other item on you and when you're battling casters put on the item that gives you the +5 to svm. It'll come in a lot more handy than an extra 2ac. Obviously your not gonan carry around a full extra suit of equipment but there are a few items you'll come across where you'll have a hard time choosing which one is better. Switching back and forth also allows you to see which one may be better &quot;for you&quot;.<br><br>There are the people who say AC is King and say it like Yosa did, and then there are the raving AC is King lunatics who seem to like playing a wimpy warrior who can take damage. <br><br>*shrug*<br><br>To each their own I guess .<br><br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Zaviax McCleo <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432</a><br><br>Shadow of the Dragon<br>Tunare<br>(www.eqsod.com)</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table