		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=126408"><span id=Sage>Bikamar</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>305 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.65]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Interesting point of view.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>You're missing a few details though.<br>You're also speaking of being the MA, the single warrior who holds agro so that only one person needs to be healed.  That's fine, but warriors have plenty of other roles as well.<br><br>AC is capped, at about 1200 (I *think* I may be wrong about the number).<br><br>Buffs are good - I love buffs (mmmm shaman, chanter mmmm :p) - unfortunately, many higher level mobs have a tendency to dispell buffs.  There's no save against dispelling (so usually have 4 junk buffs to start with).<br><br>Equipment.  Agree with you there - good gear is the best way to increase your AC - that's the reason there are so many drops for warriors as compared to other classes.  We are HEAVILY gear dependant.<br><br>A Dragon Raid is a good example of where AC is NOT king (for non-MAs).  My AC drops by about 120 on dragon raids - and my saves jump to about 100 for magic and 80 or 90 for cold or fire or whatever other save is required for that particular mob. (still working on my gear :p~)<br>Why? Because the ONLY damage I take from the dragons I have fought is from their AoE breath weapon...  and AC does squat against that.  My Sta and HPs also jump in these cases.  More HPs mean I survive maybe one or two more AoEs.<br><br>Agree with you partially about str - I like raising that, but I also like raising my dex and sta too.  Dex for procs and crits (every bit of extra damage helps) and if I am called upon to tank mez or get a guard a caster or whatever... the extra HPs give me a little longer to do that and survive til I can get a heal and someone else can grab agro (while I still deal damage to the MOB)<br><br>AC has its place.  and high AC is always good.  but it is not always the most important stat.<br><br>Oh, as for starting numbers? they don't mean all that much really - because we ARE so reliant on gear.<br><br>No offense intended. Just trying to help you see that great AC is not everything all the time. :)</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>"...come back here ya coward! I'll bite yer kneecaps off..."<br><br>It's not the class that makes the player - it's the player that makes the class</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
